do','Suspend process to background','Exit shell','Zoom in','B','Ctrl+Z suspends the current process and returns to the shell prompt.',2),(320,58,'How do you resume a suspended job in foreground?','resume','fg','continue','start','B','The fg command brings a suspended background job to the foreground.',3),(321,58,'How do you run a command in the background?','bg command','command &','command -bg','nohup command','B','Appending & to a command runs it in the background immediately.',4),(322,58,'What command lists background jobs?','ps','jobs','bg','list','B','The jobs command shows processes started from the current shell in the background.',5),(323,59,'What does man command do?','Creates manual','Displays manual pages for commands','Manages files','Monitors system','B','man shows the documentation/manual for commands, functions, and configuration files.',1),(324,59,'How do you exit man pages?','Ctrl+C','Press q','Press Escape','Type exit','B','Pressing q quits the man page viewer and returns to the prompt.',2),(325,59,'What are man page sections?','Page numbers','Categories like commands(1), system calls(2), etc.','Chapters','Versions','B','Man pages are organized into sections: 1=commands, 2=syscalls, 5=config files, etc.',3),(326,59,'How do you search within man pages?','Ctrl+F','/searchterm','grep','find','B','Type / followed by search term to search forward within man pages.',4),(327,59,'What shows a brief command description?','man -short','whatis command','info command','help command','B','whatis provides one-line descriptions from man page NAME sections.',5),(328,60,'What does cp -r do?','Copy read-only','Copy directories recursively','Copy and rename','Copy permissions','B','The -r flag enables recursive copying of directories and their contents.',3),(329,60,'What is the difference between rm and rm -rf?','No difference','rm -rf forces recursive deletion without prompts','rm -rf is safer','rm only removes directories','B','rm -rf forces deletion of directories