ents are lost when power is removed.',0),(984,197,'When should memory be captured?','After shutting down','While the system is running before shutdown','After reboot','Only during incidents','B','Memory must be captured while the system is running.',0),(985,197,'What is live forensics?','Forensics on TV','Examining a system while it is still running','Fast forensics','Video forensics','B','Live forensics analyzes running systems.',0),(986,198,'What can be found in memory dumps?','Only system files','Running processes, passwords, network connections','Only logged data','Only applications','B','Memory contains extensive runtime information.',0),(987,198,'What is a process in memory?','A factory process','A running program with its code and data','A deleted file','A backup','B','Processes are running programs with associated memory.',0),(988,198,'Can passwords be found in memory?','Never','Yes, passwords may exist in clear text in RAM','Only encrypted','Only hashed','B','Decrypted passwords often exist in memory.',0),(989,198,'What are DLLs in memory analysis?','Download links','Dynamic Link Libraries loaded by processes','Deleted files','Disk locations','B','DLLs are shared libraries loaded into process memory.',0),(990,198,'What is process injection?','Adding processes','Malware technique of inserting code into other processes','Starting processes','Killing processes','B','Process injection hides malicious code in legitimate processes.',0),(991,199,'What tools capture memory?','Screenshot tools','FTK Imager, WinPmem, or DumpIt','Video capture','Audio capture','B','Specialized tools create RAM dumps.',0),(992,199,'What is a memory dump file?','A corrupted file','A file containing the contents of RAM','An error log','A crash report only','B','Memory dumps are files containing RAM contents.',0),(993,199,'What is pagefile.sys?','A system page','Virtual memory file that may contain RAM data','A configuration file','A log file','B','The pagefile stores RAM overflow and may